  "body": "This is somehow related to #1914 and #1915.\r\n\r\nhelm version: 2.6.0\r\n\r\nThe MaxColumn is set to 60 on `helm list` and `helm history`.\r\n\r\nExample:\r\n```\r\nhelm list\r\nNAME                            \tREVISION\tUPDATED                 \tSTATUS  \tCHART                                                       \tNAMESPACE\r\nmethode-article-image-set-mapper\t5       \tFri Aug 18 15:37:00 2017\tDEPLOYED\tmethode-article-image-set-mapper-1.3.0-k28s-helm-integrat...\tdefault\r\n```\r\n\r\nCurrently there is no way to obtain the version of the chart used for the release.\r\n\r\n**Proposed solutions**:\r\n1. allow setting the column max length from the command line ``` helm list --max-col-length=6000```\r\n2. introduce another flag to show full column values ``` helm list --full-output ``` \r\n\r\n\r\n",
